NAME
    find - recursively list directory contents

SYNOPSIS
    find [path] [-type f|d]

DESCRIPTION
    Recursively walks directories and prints all file and directory
    paths, one per line. Defaults to current directory if no path given.

OPTIONS
    -type f     List only files
    -type d     List only directories

EXAMPLES
    find .
        List everything from current directory

    find /api/data
        List all models and records

    find /api/data/users -type f
        List only files (for use with xargs)

    find . | grep users
        Find paths containing "users"

    find /api/data/users -type f | xargs cat | jq .name
        Extract name from each user record

SEE ALSO
    ls, grep, xargs
